HEADWORD: Antimonic
<hw>An`ti*mon"ic</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or derived from, antimony; -- said of those
compounds of antimony in which this element has its highest equivalence;
<as>as, <ex>antimonic</ex> acid</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antimonious</ent>⟦br⟧
